                     	Aircraft data
                               
These data record six characteristics of aircraft designs which appeared
during the twentieth century.

The variables are:
	Yr:     year of first manufacture
	Period: a code to indicate one of three broad time periods
	Power:  total engine power (kW)
	Span:   wing span (m)
	Length: length (m)
	Weight: maximum take-off weight (kg)
	Speed:  maximum speed (km/h)
	Range:  range (km)
	
Source: The data were collected by P. Saviotti and are described in detail
	in Saviotti (1996), "Technological Evolution, Variety and Economy",
	Edward Elgar: Cheltenham.

